{
  "texts": [
    "The DHS can also contain thermal energy storages, i.e., insulated water tanks whose water flow can be controlled to store or release energy [29].",
    "The specific case study analysed in this work considers the AROMA DHS, presented in [24] and depicted in Figure 1.",
    "A high-fidelity dynamic simulator based on a dedicated Modelica library [30] serves as a digital twin to generate input-output data for training the data-based models and to act as the real physical system for control simulations.The following system variables are considered as inputs and outputs for the data-based model, as shown in Figure 1 and described in [31].",
    "The manipulated (control) variables are the supply temperature at the heating station, denoted by T s 0, and the water flow from the thermal storage, denoted by q TES.",
    "The external disturbances are the five thermal load demands, i.e., P c j for j = 1,..., 5, with the overall input vector thus defined as u = [T s 0 q TES P c 1... P c 5] ⊤."
  ]
}